cks''\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Album\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \u2013\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| 1981\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Peristyle\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \"I'm Out of Lies\"\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Single\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \u2013\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| 1981\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Peristyle\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \"Childsplay\"\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Single\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \u2013\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| 1982\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Alan Spears\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \"Take This Heart\"\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Single\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \u2013\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| 1982\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Alan Spears\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \"Hard Times for Lovers\"\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Single\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \u2013\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| 1983\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Maya\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| ''Murder by Love''\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Album\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \u2013\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| 1984\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Joe Savage\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \"Out of Control\"\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Single\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \u2013\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| 1984\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Lee Marquette\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \"Tease Me\"\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Single\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \u2013\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| 1984\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Joe Savage and the Joe Savage Band\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \"Don't Let It Go\"\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Single\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \u2013\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| 1984\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Joe Savage and the Joe Savage Band\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \"Life\"\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Single\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \u2013\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| 1984\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| [[Billy Lee Riley]]\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \"Rock 'n' Roll Money\"\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Single\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \u2013\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| 1984\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| [[Billy Lee Riley]]\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \"Old time Rock 'n' Roll\"\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Single\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \u2013\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| 1984\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Terry Rose\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \"Southern Comfort\"\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Single\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \u2013\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| 1984\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Memphis\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \"Gone But Not Forgotten\"\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Single\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \u2013\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| 1984\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Gary McCrary\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \"Texas Tornado\"\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Single\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \u2013\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| 1984\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Gary McCrary\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \"Louisiana Purchase\"\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Single\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \u2013\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| 1985\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Palomino\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \"Twin Silver Running\"\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Single\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \u2013\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| 1985\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Palomino\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \"Photographic Memory\"\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Single\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \u2013\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| 1985\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Shock Therapy\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| ''Shock Therapy''\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Album\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \u2013\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| 1986\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| [[B.B. King]]\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \"Standing on the Edge of Love\"\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Single\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| from ''[[The Color of Money]] soundtrack''. 1988 Grammy Nomination for Best Contemporary Blues Recording<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.awardsandshows.com/features/grammy-awards-1988-236.html |title=Grammy Awards 1988}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| 1987\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| [[Dave Mason]]\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| ''Two Hearts''\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Album\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| featuring [[Steve Winwood]] and [[Phoebe Snow]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/two-hearts-mw0000193141 |title=Two Hearts - Dave Mason}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| 1987\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| [[Dave Mason]] and [[Phoebe Snow]]\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \"The Dreams I Dream\"\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Single\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| US AC No. 11 featuring [[Phoebe Snow]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/dave-mason/chart-history/adult-contemporary/song/379688 |title=Dave Mason Dreams I Dream Chart History}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| 1987\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| [[Dave Mason]]\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \"Fighting for Love\"\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Single\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| -\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| 1988\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| [[Dave Mason]] featuring [[Steve Winwood]]\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| \"Something in the Heart\"\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| Single\n| style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"| US Mainstream Rock No. 24 featuring [[Steve Winwood]]<ref>{{C